linefit.FitAlgorithms

Enum FitType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FitType>
      • linefit.FitAlgorithms.FitType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FitType>

    public enum FitType
extends java.lang.Enum<FitType>
    This enumeration is used to keep track of the FitType and handles its basic functions that allow it to be treated as a string or a number
    • NONE - Don't show fit
    • REGULAR - Show fit but don't factor errors into the fit
    • X_ERROR - Factor horizontal errors into the fit only
    • Y_ERROR - Factor vertical errors into the fit only
    • BOTH_ERRORS - Factor both horizontal errors and vertical errors into the fit
    Since:
    <0.98.0
    Version:
    1.2
    Author:
    Keith Rice
